Adam Macchia for The New York Times
Reported by Jill P. Capuzzo and Marcelle Sussman Fischler
Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York and New Jersey:
• In Islip, N.Y., a six-bedroom, five-and-a-half-bath renovated 1970 house with a paver parking court with a fountain, an office, a billiard room, a cabana, an in-ground pool, an outdoor kitchen, an attached one-car garage, a koi pond and a private sandy beach.
• In Colts Neck, N.J., a five-bedroom, three-full- and two-half-bath brick and stucco-faced recently updated 1984 house, with a great room with a wood-burning fireplace and vaulted wood-beamed ceiling, an open kitchen and breakfast room, a first-floor master bedroom suite, a finished basement with a home theater and an attached three-car garage.
